svg.text: The chart below is a generated representation of sorts of the family tree of human language scripts, beginning with Proto Cuneiform
in approximately 3400BC, and continuing through *all scripts in history. The information is gleaned from Wikipedia pages of the scripts.
(* It is still a work in progress.) Each script shown gives its genealogy: ancestors and children. Its placement on the horizontal axis
indicates its approximate beginning of use, and the width indicates its duration. The colors of the bars indicates the type of script.
Still undeciphered scripts have a dashed oval. You can click on the bar of any script to go to the representative wikipedia page.
